<BYLINE>By DAVID ESPO</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Flattery is the first and firmest rule in the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION>, but in a single day the debate on Defense Secretary-designate <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Tower </PERSON> produced a series of mutual attacks on integrity, motives and competence. Senate Republican Leader <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Dole </PERSON> touched off Tuesday's fireworks when he announced that <ORGANIZATION> Armed </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Sam </PERSON> <PERSON> Nunn </PERSON>, D-Ga., had detailed investigators to check new allegations against Tower `` Partisan unit,'' <PERSON> Dole </PERSON> later called it. `` Strike force.'' `` Highly questionable if not inappropriate,'' Republican Sen. <PERSON> Arlen </PERSON> <PERSON> Specter </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION> said. `` I think it needs to be pursued to see where it leads us.'' <PERSON> Nunn </PERSON>, leader of the Tower opposition, defended himself a short while later by saying he had been informed the <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> would no longer look into allegations against Tower. He then was asked about Republican claims that his effort to derail Tower is really an attempt to grab power for himself at the Pentagon, or perhaps jockey for position in the 1992 White House campaign. `` It's an onslaught,'' he said, `` The basic rule is if you do n't have the facts on your side, you try to destroy the credibility of someone who is presenting them on the other side So I think that formula is in full effect right now.'' And when Democrat <PERSON> Dennis </PERSON> <PERSON> DeConcini </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Arizona </LOCATION> said that an <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> report on Tower turned up evidence of `` wrongdoing,'' Republican <PERSON> Warren </PERSON> <PERSON> Rudman </PERSON> of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hampshire </LOCATION> replied tartly. That was n't so, he said _ at least not t