<HEAD>Guilty Verdict in `Ski Mask Rapist' Case</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Note contents of last graf.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A man convicted of being the `` ski mask rapist'' in the sexual assaults of 26 women is virtually assured of spending the rest of his life in prison, a prosecutor said. <PERSON> Anthony </PERSON> <PERSON> Sanchez </PERSON>, a 27-year-old former city sewer worker, was found guilty Tuesday of 117 of 136 charges stemming from the assaults. `` If I just look at the violent sexual offenses, I can see that he's looking at more than 500 years in prison,'' prosecutor <PERSON> Margo </PERSON> <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> said. Disregarding appeals, <PERSON> Sanchez </PERSON> would have to serve at least half his sentence before being eligible for parole. `` We have a number of victims here who were greatly traumatized. There can be no doubt justice has been done,'' <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> said. Superior Court Judge <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Teilh </PERSON> set sentencing for April 25. <PERSON> Teilh </PERSON> said he had carefully reviewed preliminary hearing transcripts and found no doubt that <PERSON> Sanchez </PERSON> was guilty of most of the counts filed against him. <PERSON> Sanchez </PERSON> agreed Friday to let the judge declare a verdict based on the transcripts, which included testimony from the victims. <PERSON> Teilh </PERSON> dismissed 19 charges. Police reports said <PERSON> Sanchez </PERSON> usually stalked his victims before accosting them and often tied them up, sexually assaulting them, then taking cash, jewelry or automatic bank-teller cards. The rapes occurred in both homes and offices and one woman was attacked in a church confessional. The assailant usually wore a ski mask and often threatened his victims with a knife or pellet gun that closely resembled a .45 - caliber `` I've killed before, and I'll kill again,'' he warned them, according to the police reports. When <PERSON> Sanchez </PERSON> was arrested Dec. 16, 1987, police discovered a ski mask, a black pellet gun and a hooded sweat shirt in his car. Several victims said their assailant had worn such a mask and shirt. The charges against <PERSON> Sanchez </PERSON> involved attacks from 1985 to 1987 on <LOCATION> Santa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Clara </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> women ranging in age from 16 to 84. Teilh found <PERSON> Sanchez </PERSON> guilty on 22 counts each of rape, burglary, and robbery. He also found <PERSON> Sanchez </PERSON> guilty of 23 oral copulation charges, six assaults with intent to commit rape, 17 sexual batteries, four instances of sodomy and one count of penetration with a foreign object.
