<HEAD>Lawyer Enters Innocent Plea For Congressman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Rep. <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Lukens </PERSON> has pleaded innocent on a misdemeanor charge accusing him of having sex with a teen-age girl. <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> Tyack </PERSON>, one of two attorneys representing <ORGANIZATION> Lukens </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> R-Ohio </LOCATION>, entered the plea Tuesday in <LOCATION> Franklin </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> Juvenile Court. <PERSON> Tyack </PERSON> also requested a jury trial before Judge <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> <PERSON> Solove </PERSON>. No date has been set for the trial. A grand jury on Feb. 23 indicted <ORGANIZATION> Lukens </ORGANIZATION> on a charge of contributing to the unruliness and delinquency of a child. The charge alleges that <ORGANIZATION> Lukens </ORGANIZATION> had sex with a 16-year-old girl last November. <ORGANIZATION> Lukens </ORGANIZATION> has denied the charge and said he was the victim of a `` setup'' by the girl, who he said was seeking money. The indictment came after a television station broadcast a secretly recorded videotape in which the girl's mother asked <ORGANIZATION> Lukens </ORGANIZATION> why he was `` messin' around'' with her teen-age daughter. <ORGANIZATION> Lukens </ORGANIZATION> replied that he did not know the girl was a teen-ager, the station said.
