<HEAD>Apartment Fire In France Kills 11</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELFORT, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Fire swept through a five-story apartment building in this eastern city today, killing 11 people and injuring eight, fire officials said. An undetermined number of people were missing, said a fire department official who spoke on condition of anonymity. The fire broke out about 3:30 a.m., and 80 firefighters brought it under control about two hours later, he said. He said the fire started in a third-floor stairway but that the cause had not been determined. Four people died of injuries suffered when they jumped out of windows on the upper floors of the old building, located near the local university, the official said. Four bodies were found in the ravaged building soon after the fire was extinguished, and three more were found later by fire investigators. The fire official said five residents of the building and three firefighters were injured.
