years ago that forced President <PERSON> Anwar </PERSON> <PERSON> Sadat </PERSON> to roll back increases. At least 79 people were killed in the 1977 riots, with some estimates of the casualties going to 800 killed and injured. `` We agree with the <ORGANIZATION> IMF </ORGANIZATION> on the diagnosis and the prescription, but we differ on the amount of time to implement it,'' said one source. <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION>, which already has increased prices on bread and other basic commodities five to ten times in recent years, would like to phase in the reforms over a few years, he said. `` Ideally we would like very much to implement the reforms at the same pace recommended by the <ORGANIZATION> IMF </ORGANIZATION>, but it's a question of practicality,'' he said, adding that the Egyptian government hoped `` <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, as an ally and friend, would be more sensitive to our political and social circumstances than a bank.'' `` We regard the relationship with <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION> as extremely important, both to us as well as to the interest of broader stability in the region,'' <PERSON> Redman </PERSON> said. He said the aid, a portion of about $ 4.5 billion in economic and military assistance approved for the 1988 and 1989 fiscal years, was being held up because the legislation approved by <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> made it contingent on `` the understanding that <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION> will undertake significant economic reforms which are additional to those which were undertaken in previous fiscal years.''
