es. On the foreign exchange market, the dollar ended at 128.73 yen, 0.30 yen lower than Tuesday's 129.03-yen finish. The dollar opened at 128.68 yen and ranged between 128.65 yen and 128.90 yen. `` The dollar-yen rate has hardly moved since around 10 a.m.,'' said a dealer with <ORGANIZATION> Mitsubishi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION>, also requesting anonymity. He also cited caution before announcement of the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> jobless figures. Meanwhile, <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Japan </ORGANIZATION> Governor <PERSON> Satoshi </PERSON> <PERSON> Sumita </PERSON> told a news conference today that he did not see foreign exchange rates as likely to fluctuate widely, but added that the central bank was prepared to `` take appropriate measures'' if rates showed significant changes.
