<HEAD>Cookie Giant Buying Out Local Noodle Maker</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOLUCA, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Tortellini, ravioli and manicotti will soon be added to the cookies, crackers and snacks sold by <ORGANIZATION> Keebler </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> if the proposed buyout of a Toluca-based frozen pasta manufacturer goes through as planned. <ORGANIZATION> Keebler </ORGANIZATION> has signed a letter of intent to purchase <ORGANIZATION> Bernardi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Italian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foods </ORGANIZATION> _ a family business which traces its roots to 1932 and a small restaurant run by the son of <LOCATION> Italian </LOCATION> immigrants. Today, <PERSON> Bernardi </PERSON> employs about 120 people in the production of about 40 varieties of fresh and frozen pasta which it distributes nationally and in <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION>. `` They are going through our books right now and we're supposed to close the deal in mid-April,'' <PERSON> Jerry </PERSON> <PERSON> Bernardi </PERSON>, chief executive of the pasta company, said Tuesday. Terms of the proposed sale were not disclosed. `` But nothing is going to change here,'' <PERSON> Bernardi </PERSON> said. `` It's going to be business as usual and everything will remain under the <LOCATION> Bernardi </LOCATION> label We will be a subsidiary of <ORGANIZATION> Keebler </ORGANIZATION>, operated independently. My son, <PERSON> Dick </PERSON>, and I are even going to continue to run it.'' <ORGANIZATION> Keebler </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Stuart </PERSON> <PERSON> Greenblatt </PERSON>, at company headquarters in the <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> suburb of <LOCATION> Elmhurst </LOCATION>, said the purchase of <PERSON> Bernardi </PERSON> was tentative and requires the approval of <ORGANIZATION> Keebler </ORGANIZATION>'s parent company, <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Biscuits </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> -LRB- </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holdings </ORGANIZATION> -RRB- PLC of <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Greenblatt </PERSON> said the