<SECOND>AM-Oil Prices,0244</SECOND>
<HEAD>Energy Futures Head Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Energy futures prices rose Wednesday, driven by market rumors and technical factors. The April contract for the benchmark grade of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> crude oil, <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> Intermediate, settled 24 cents higher at $ 18.54 a barrel, regaining some of the ground lost Tuesday when the contract fell 37 cents on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> Among refined petroleum products traded on the exchange, the April contract for wholesale home heating oil settled 0.29 cent higher at 51.37 cents a gallon, after falling 0.35 cent the previous session. April unleaded gasoline, which lost 0.18 cent on Tuesday, rose 0.44 cent to 51.85 cents a gallon. `` Having settled on a sour note Tuesday night ... the market has really turned around,'' said <PERSON> Mary </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Haskins </PERSON>, a vice president at <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Burnham </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lambert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc </ORGANIZATION>. Some of incentive for the turnaround came from reports circulating in the market of a conflict between <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION>. Before details of the reported conflict filtered fully through the market, energy futures rallied temporarily with dealers buying in speculation that tensions between the two <LOCATION> Persian </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> countries might cause supply disruptions. The buying lost momentum once it became clear in the market that the conflict referred to an incident that occurred in mid-February. But at the same time, the rally drove crude past technical price thresholds that triggered more buying, <PERSON> Haskins </PERSON> said.
</TEXT>
