<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Natural gas from <LOCATION> Wyoming </LOCATION> will flow to <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> under an agreement announced Wednesday between <ORGANIZATION> Pacific </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Gas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electric </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> and a unit of Houston-based <ORGANIZATION> Coastal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. Coastal's <ORGANIZATION> Wyoming-California </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pipeline </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> said <ORGANIZATION> PG </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; E has agreed to withdraw its opposition to WyCal's proposal to provide new interstate natural gas pipeline capacity to <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> WyCal will provide interstate shippers on WyCal's proposed pipeline system with the option in <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> of utilizing WyCal's pipeline or a Federal Energy Regulatory Commission-regulated expansion of <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco-based </LOCATION> <ORGANIZATION> PG </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; E's existing facilities for transportation within <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> In January, the regulatory commission authorized WyCal to construct and operate a 650 million cubic feet per day natural gas pipeline system from the Overthrust producing region in <LOCATION> Wyoming </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> Kern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif </LOCATION>. Through interconnections with other pipelines, the WyCal system also can transport Canadian natural gas. Under either alternative, shippers would be assured of <ORGANIZATION> FERC </ORGANIZATION> regulation of their transportation contracts for up to 25 years. After 25 years, jurisdiction would be subject to regulation by the <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Public </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Utilities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> PG </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; E has been granted the right to purchase 50 million cubic feet a day of firm transportation capacity on WyCal's system for 20 years. If <ORGANIZATION> PG </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; E exercises that right, it can acquire a 25 percent ownership interest in the WyCal system.
